production environment cannot be set as the active sync target — use
ggt pull --env production to pull production files instead.

USAGE
  ggt env use <name> [flags]

ARGUMENTS
  name
        Environment name. The production environment cannot be set as the active
        sync target.

FLAGS
  -a, --app, --application <app>
        Gadget app to use. The app slug is the subdomain portion of your app URL
        (e.g., my-app from my-app.gadget.app). Can be omitted when
        .gadget/sync.json already records the app.

EXAMPLES
  $ ggt env use staging
  $ ggt env use development
"
`;

